##A neighborhood in Wuhan wants to be disinfected

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Ge mingning, an intern from Wuhan, Zhang Zhuo, Shen Qingqing, and Lan Zeqi, is a reporter for the paper

The decontamination process has begun.

The atomizer, shaped like a pistol, gurgled white smoke and rumbled. Armed employees of the disinfection company, shouldering equipment, sprayed from the first floor to the seventh floor.

Wuhan began a three-day sweep on February 17 to "round up" new coronavirus infections, suspected cases, close contacts and four groups of people with fever.

In this old community located on the West Bank of the Yangtze River, "disinfection" is the most urgent desire. The occasional ambulance ride in and out of the neighborhood, and the workers in white protective suits, breed all kinds of imagination, including rumors. Homeowners are posting on social media, demanding that communities sanitize more frequently.

Although the community response, many people fear the building did not have a patient, "please residents do not believe rumors, do not spread rumors, " but they eventually invited the disinfection team.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 17, disinfection began, lasting three or four days.

Corridor filled with atomized disinfection water, and other residential areas in Wuhan, February 20, here into the "closed management" mode.

For now, it has been days since they left their homes, and the anxiety seems to be as intense as buying groceries and medicines, or as a result of suspicious "changes" in the neighborhood.

A small community in Wuhan is experiencing complex emotional ups and downs during the outbreak.

1
1

1

The community looks old, more than 3,000 residents of the elderly accounted for the majority. In mid-to-late February, the "four groups of people" was cleared of the last moment. But in a residential building deep in the neighborhood, some people still suspect that there are missing patients.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Completed in 2000, the complex is located in a remote area and is mostly occupied by elderly people.

Wang Fengying on the second floor is in her 50s. She told reporters through the screen door that material stress was understandable, but that something in the neighborhood made her feel like she was on her way to Florida

There is a chess and card room at the gate of the community, owned by an old lady under seventy. Wang Fengying's husband often goes to play cards and is well acquainted with his family. The shopkeeper was seen going to the hospital for oxygen years ago and was said to have had a fever.

"We had only heard about her high blood pressure and cervical spondylosis. After she became ill, we made several video calls repeatedly to ask after her. All of them were answered by her family and always said she was fine. "

Later, the woman shop owner died, the family said the cause of death was acute myocardial infarction, but Wang Fengying did not believe. At the time, wechat groups in the community were warning not to approach patients and their families, and residents would take a detour.

She would like to ask the owner of the real cause of death, but "we are not easy to inquire, ask, as if we want to see her family's joke. ".

Wang Fengying had two relatives in their 80s who had been diagnosed as "new crown" patients. Their beds were tight at the time, and they did not make it to the hospital, where they died in late January. At the end of their lives, they were pulled from their homes to an emergency center and then to a funeral home.

Wang Fengying thinks she is still young. But from time to time among her classmates, someone mentioned the death of a friend of the same age. To Wang Fengying, they were all famous people, and her heart could not stop shaking.

"There's no way out. It's a sudden outbreak. The hospital can't handle it. We're too old and our resistance is weak. There's no special medicine for this disease. We just have to fight with our immunity. "

Before the community closed management, she is not willing to take a step out of the house, if not the family to eat and drink words.

She goes out every two or three days, goes home, sprays her clothes with disinfectant, and hangs them on the balcony. She used up a bag of booties. Sorry she didn't have her "glasses. ". She is always in a panic when she has to go out to take out the rubbish.

As she spoke, Wang Fengying scanned the empty corridor. Maybe there were fever patients upstairs, but she hid herself and would not say anything. She told reporters she was looking forward to disinfecting the entire building.

1
2
1

2

From time to time there are ambulances and white vans to take patients parked in front of the community. A photo of the car was taken and circulated on the owner-built Wechat Group: a White Car drove out.

Information about life, such as spontaneous group purchases of face masks and food, is mostly available, but sometimes "clues" of outbreaks circulate here.

I heard that the community has added a confirmed case, "who can tell me when it took away? " A young head asked, "I in the afternoon in the outside... who can tell me with (virus) brush past? "

"people are cars in building x, unit x, " said another.

"there was a car going in, and it seemed to argue with the man at the door, and I looked at it... and when I came out, I showed a little bit of my head here in the guard's room. " She gave several weeping looks.

The owners tried to restore the origin and spread of the "epidemic" in the district.

Wang Fengying's friend, Jiang Xiaomei, who lives on the third floor, confirmed that the disease was spread by the community's elderly dance team eating New Year's Eve dinner. When they came back, some of them had fevers, some of them were hospitalized.

Jiang Xiaomei surmised, dance team in some aunt love face, they got sick, May "Yin" do not say, usually they and husband quarrel will not say.

"I heard that a woman's husband has been coughing, " Jiang Xiaomei said to reporters mysteriously. She is an old woman with a strong voice. Jiang Xiaomei has always disliked the dance team  Furthermore, the dance team and the residential property get too close, and Jiang Xiaomei is dissatisfied with the property.

She complained that the property dinner "cheap" , carrying a pot of round son up, the property on the pour away, to take home. "I said you ate well this time. Everyone went to the hospital. "

Since the rumor spread that the virus originated from New Year's Eve dinner, some people in the community asked around, that table, which a few people sit.

In Jiang Xiaomei upstairs, the sixth floor of the residents Qiu Lan analysis, a number of close contacts running outside. For example, a young woman dressed in black, as if she showed a photo of a woman in a black down jacket, but she didn't recognize the girl in the picture.

Images like this are also from the owner group. The view from the apartment building, which is said to have been taken the day before. There is also a watermark on the picture, "the father has been diagnosed. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Residents often see ambulances coming and going, and photos are circulating on Wechat. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Qiu Lan, who is in her 50s, was excited. "Her father is already in hospital. She should report it to quarantine. She's carrying the virus. It's killing all of us! "

Qiu Lan himself lives with his son and daughter-in-law. She struggled to get permission to bring in her daughter-in-law's grandmother, who usually lives alone. She's got a lot on her plate right now.

Some owners called the community to demand total eradication, when the epidemic was at its worst, the community said there were not enough people. The owners also referred to "the girl in the black down jacket" and asked the community to impose a mandatory quarantine on her.

The community responded that her father had not been diagnosed, and that was a rumor. So the owners called the mayor's hotline to complain about the community leaders. Some owners see the patient's family out to buy things, chose to report to the police.

"The tone of the community is tougher than ours, " said Qiu Lan's son, who has a heart condition and continues to wheeze. Don't worry, Qiu Lan. It's not a virus.

Wang Nan, a seventh-floor resident, is sympathetic to the community. He feels that the community and property staff have little protection and work outdoors. Like the medical staff, they are "fighting for their lives. " He does not want to burden them.

Wang Nan and his wife, both in their late 20s, have set up a vegetable plot on the top floor, picking vegetables for daily use, and have not been downstairs for a month.

Wang, who speaks slowly, said he was a retired cadre originally from Henan and had been working in Wuhan. He wanted to complain about something, but he stopped. "What can I say, girl? What can I say? "

1

The whole building felt that the disinfection should be responsible for the property, and the property manager told the reporter that there were dozens of buildings and about a dozen property personnel in the community, three of whom were gate keepers, two of whom were administrators, and the rest were electricians and cleaners. The property can't clear all the hallways.

Qiu Lan recommended that the reporter go to see a warm-hearted owner Liu Zhengkai. This is a tall, fat young man, 27-year-old fitness coach, he introduced himself, early love to play, like fighting, but now has changed.

One day, Liu Zhengkai recalled, he was pouring tea on his balcony. When he saw a stretcher carrying the patient out, he felt only a surge of blood and Qi. At that moment, he felt he had to stand up and organize a joint "fight against the epidemic" .

At a bookstore not far from the gym, he read a copy of Barnard's organization and management. He immediately formulated a plan: In the community to recruit young volunteers, preferably 30-year-old unmarried, under 40 can also, each building to recruit a person, unified out of the purchase. A batch of disinfectants will also be procured centrally and disinfected by young volunteers. The rest of the time, no one leaves the house.

This is what happened a few days before the reporter met him. But on Feb. 13, Liu Zhengkai was a little frustrated: He sent his Wechat Qr code to the community's Wechat group and then looped it around the community with a loudspeaker at night, calling on residents to participate in the war on drugs, but no young people came to join him on Wechat.

You have kids, so be safe and don't go out, said Liu Zhengkai, a 40 year old neighbor whose sister wanted to volunteer. Several 60-year-old people also added to his wechat. Liu Zhengkai thought it was no different from harming people's lives. He turned them all down.

Later, the community secretary explained to the reporter that there were many elderly people in the community -- as if there had been an activity called "neighborhood care" , in which 60-year-old volunteers bought groceries for 80-year-old runners. Before, Liu Zhengkai never participated in the community's social activities, early to go home late he only knew a young neighbor.

Liu zhengkai disinfected his building with a small pot used to water the flowers. He felt that the rumors in the community were a bit excessive, so he stood alone at the gate, recording the frequency of the daily delivery of patients.

Because the owners of a family has not yet sent a confirmed patient, Liu Zhengkai decided to personally verify the true and false, he deliberately chose the night, so there must be someone at home. Before going out, he even put on the Zhongkui pendant that drives away evil spirits, the result proves to be a rumor, there is no person living in that unit.

Liu Zhengkai went out to disinfect, a little nervous. He wore a Zhong Kui pendant to ward off evil spirits. Photo courtesy of the respondents

"All they do is pass around pictures and talk nonsense, " said Liu, who later became cynical.

But he understood how they felt. On the second day of the interview, he also sent a photo of the woman in the black down jacket. "The whole building is scared to death, " Liu said. "Can you check it out? "

He has a friend whose mother has a fever and lives on the roof of a building. Downstairs out of the "new crown" confirmed patients, that night, Liu Zhengkai six out of his mind, and the reporter to discuss whether to send patients downstairs to see a doctor, "will be through the door of the confirmed patients.

Finally, the friend's mother went to see a doctor and was diagnosed with "new crown" pneumonia.

4
1

4

"You have a hard time making sense with them. " When the reporter saw Zhou Wenshan, the community secretary in charge of the community, he looked very upset.

"Some people complain that the property is only sprayed with water at the entrance to the building. How is this possible? Some people want to kill the whole building. The property manager says even the property in the high-end residential area can not do it. Can residents listen to such words? "

Property management is generally under the direction of the Housing Authority. Zhou Wenshan said that the community usually lets the property do some work, relies on the personal sentiment. In the "four categories of personnel" "zero" at the moment, Zhou Wenshan no longer pay attention to the contradictions between residents and properties.

On February 13, he was busy persuading close contacts to go to the quarantine point. According to the people in the street office, Zhou spent a night in front of a resident's house  As if persuasion were a mechanical thing. He kept saying the same thing to people until he coaxed them into a car.

"isolation is for your safety, and for the safety of your family. The government spends all this money for the good of your people. It's not you who's in trouble. You're in good health. If someone in your house is a little... it's not worth it. You don't have to pay a penny for food and drink at the isolation point."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The community service center is located in an alley at the edge of the town

Nearly half the population needs Zhou Wenshan to repeat the same mantra. On February 19, the reporter saw him for the second time, and still did.

He was picking up a phone call from a colleague on the other end, who said it didn't make sense, that a close contact didn't want to take the covers to the isolation point. Zhou Wenshan said: "Then we can not buy it, you say is not, you say can buy? "

After the hotel was changed to a quarantine point, they "rushed" to send in close contacts. Otherwise, a new diagnosis would immediately add many more close contacts and many more variables.

The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention in all districts of Wuhan have the identity information of "four categories of people" in streets and communities. In addition to each street Chengguan and volunteers are responsible for driving, Zhou Wenshan's district requires community cadres to personally put "four categories of people" into the car to complete the handover. If it's a confirmed case, the street office will send someone to follow.

So on the afternoon of February 19, Zhou twice laboriously slipped himself into an industrial-grade protective suit. He said that most of the community cadres are women, timid. And he's a 55-year-old man. This is a matter of contact with patients and close contacts, if you take turns to go back to the community service center prone to cross-infection. With that, he rode off in a "community patrol" battery-powered car.

Before this, listen to the reporter to mention that strong demand disinfection of the community, Zhou Wenshan face of boredom and add a layer. There was a close contact in the neighborhood who didn't want to go to the quarantine site, he recalled. It was very difficult.

Finally, he angrily said to the woman: "You community Wechat group is in curse you. Or, you write a pledge, the owner later hit, do not find me. " The other party listened, asked to immediately to quarantine point. It was a night, and there was no car. Zhou Wenshan led her on a 2.5 km night walk.

5
1

5

Sitting in front of reporters, Zhou Wenshan said, just before the experience are combed again.

The Community Service Center has a staff of more than a dozen, except for one person in charge of data, others are busy with trivial matters. There are more than 10,000 people in the district, and some of the residents make outlandish demands. Some obviously 60-year-old, children only live a kilometer away, but said he was already 80 years old, to the community to bring him food. Zhou felt he shouldn't, but he was worried about the complaint. Every time a resident calls the mayor's hotline, or even the police, they have to file paperwork.

When there is no epidemic, the request to the residents, the community cadres will do household verification, generally only childless widows and the elderly, disabled, can enjoy special care. However, Zhou Wenshan now does not want to send people to the residents'homes. The demand of those who deliver medicine to deliver vegetables, can only promise to come down first, deliver to the resident entrance.

He said he couldn't spare the men to disinfect it. Even if there are volunteers willing to disinfection, contact with the patient, Zhou Wenshan will not be allowed. This was a risk, and even if the volunteers didn't blame him, their parents and friends would call the mayor's hotline and the police.

It all happened so fast, he said.

On January 23, Wuhan was "sealed off" . It was December twenty-nine, and a stranger came to the community service center to ask him for a certificate. They thought the community would allow them to leave Wuhan, but Zhou could not prove it. He also thought that when the epidemic was over, these people would go home for the Lantern Festival.

On the first night of the Lunar New Year, Zhou moved into his office on the second floor of the community service center. He did not return home for more than 20 days. His phone's always connected to a charger. During the first few days of the Lunar New Year, a large number of patients' families couldn't get through to "110" or "120" , so they called him -- his number was written on a bulletin board in the community.

The most tense time, is the first month third, the fourth day, he did not sleep. Wuhan that two days fell light rain, to the fifth day, into the sleet. Zhou Wenshan hung up a phone, can see just could not call in, call back in the past, that end is to his plea: I am in the House, burning to death.

But there weren't enough beds, so he said to the patients, "that's all we have in the community. I'll report you to the street tomorrow. ".

During that time, Zhou Wenshan did not take off his shoes to sleep, nor did he turn off the lights.

Some female patients get sick at home, and the community can't help her. Her son-in-law came to the community service center first to yell at her. The next day, he was still unable to be hospitalized. Her daughter came to the community, took off her mask, and let out a gasp.

On February 2nd, "loose" . At the beginning of the day, the patients were admitted to the hospital. But Zhou Wenshan was very tired: Some people with fever attacked him late at night and said he did not serve them; after the supply of hospital beds increased, some people even exaggerated their condition and wanted to be hospitalized quickly; others wanted to send money to Zhou Wenshan, this made him feel "insulted" .

Recently, Zhou Wenshan was delivering vegetables to the elderly. He said he was very happy to deliver food. Although he was tired from climbing the stairs, the old people thanked him.

6
1

6

"It is impossible to deliver protective clothing according to the quantity, " Liu Ning, director of the sub-district office, told reporters, "The district just gives a rough estimate of what the streets are going to need. Sometimes, to save on the suits, the patients are taken downstairs for a while. It saves one. "

It was Liu Ning who saved the suit. He explained on behalf of the district government that the reason for requiring grassroots cadres to transport patients themselves was that when they arrived at the hospital reception, patients would stand "very scattered" on their own initiative to avoid cross-infection and needed to be kept in order.

Liu Ning and the officer in charge of driving had been to the shelter hospital twice. On the morning of Feb. 15, Ms. Liu paced the hallways of the neighborhood office, making phone calls to close contacts. Close contacts that the community secretary couldn't handle were also transferred to Liu Ning.

But Liu says he does not have the difficulties of a community cadre. "They deal with a lot of people, we deal with a limited number of people. "

During the special period, the original organization system of the Community Office was broken up and divided into the transportation group, the material group and the data group. The transport team dispatches converted Chengguan vehicles to serve as temporary ambulances to transport patients; the supply team delivers daily supplies to patients at the isolation sites, bringing back alcohol and boxes of Chinese medicine from the district government for distribution to the communities; The data set provides real-time updates on cases in each community, including temperature, nucleic acid test results, and close contacts of each confirmed patient.

Wang Jia of the data group is in the Wechat Group of the District Center for Disease Control. At the busiest time, the group will pop up late at night, said that a hospital has beds, please report the patient's latest situation on the streets. Wang Jia was busy sending emails to the district CDC, including the personal information and chest film of the seriously ill patients in the district. Wang always felt that he was racing against other streets.

At that time, in order to determine the list, Liu Ning and Wang Jia to report to the community to the seriously ill patients line up, the priorities. Liu said that community secretaries had different stories in their materials, some were especially nervous, some might have collected too many cases in their districts, and the descriptions were understated.

At first, Liu Ning will find the street health center to look at the chest film, but later the center director infected with the "new crown" virus, there is no more than one doctor to help him.

Liu Ning is asthma patient, "to cough asthma of matter quite understand" , so he oneself calls the family member of serious disease patient. Sometimes he would think, what if he was wrong, "well, we'll just have to do our best. ".

He said of a 35-year-old "new crown" patient with asthma, "I'm fine, " the patient said by phone. "Let someone else have the bed. ".

After a while, the patient's wife to call Liu Ning, said while crying. Actually, the patient's not doing so well. Later, Liu Ning sent him to Tongji Hospital in the French new city hospital district.

When the shelter hospital began to treat patients, there are a few days, the designated hospital to receive critically ill patients is still quite full, liuning want to let the patients in the area to be admitted to the hospital in time.

"We had to take a static Oxygenation test to get into the shelter, " Liu recalled. "I told the patients to be calm on the way to the shelter. Don't be impatient. A Oxygenation will fall. "

On February 15, Liu Ning had one thing to report to the district government: There was a uremic patient under the age of 30 who tested negative for nucleic acid, but was a "new crown" patient who met the clinical diagnostic criteria. He did not want to go to the shelter hospital because it was not convenient to go to another hospital for dialysis and there was a risk of cross-infection. Liu Ning would like to ask the district there is no compromise.

His other assignment was to prepare a gated community. In liuning district, many residential buildings directly facing the road. We'll have to organize and close the roads.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The sub-district office wants to close the road. It's snowing. We got ta get it done before it freezes.

Sterilization is just one of the many things they have to do.

"epidemic" after the outbreak, as long as someone died at home, regardless of whether there are signs of a "new crown" related to the interior of the house to be thoroughly killed. Zheng Yun, sitting diagonally opposite Wang Jia, is responsible for collecting information on the deaths of community members, docking district CDC to disinfection, to coordinate their vehicles.

She was also responsible for cross-checking close contacts. When a case is confirmed, the district checks in with the patient, then sends her a list of close contacts, which she calls to review and reloads. After a while, the district will give Wang Jia a definitive version of the list of close contacts. Wang then distributed the list to the communities to persuade them to accept the quarantine.

But as "one of" disinfection, residents in the eyes of the moment is extremely urgent.

Liu Ning hand-off Zheng Yun, contact can do the community outside the third party. In the aforementioned work gap, Zheng Yun made several phone calls, the first said he was working in the isolation point, the second shut down, the third said, the price of killing a building is 700 yuan. Zheng Yun feels a bit expensive, she is not sure by which funds out of this money.

It took three or four days before and after disinfection, and the mist rolled inside and outside.

"Now residents are also afraid, so let them feel safe. " In an interview on the 19th, Zhou said he persuaded the property manager to pay for a disinfection. Otherwise, he did not know what to do.

The community has been closed. February 20, property manager Zhang in the coordination of residents to buy vegetables. He told the reporter, don't listen to the residents scold us, the annual property costs of this community, but 60 cents per square meter, this money can do what?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After the completion of the "four categories of personnel zero" , the main work of the community is to protect the livelihood of the people. Turnips and winter melons were piled up at the gate.

During the outbreak, an electrician fell down at the property. He was about 52 years old, tall and thin, from Huangpi District, Wuhan, and his wife was also sick. The Doorman said that the residents had been nervous about seeing the electrician leave the house and had called the police.

As for the young woman in the black down jacket, the documents from the street office show that her mother was admitted to the hospital on January 30 as a "newly crowned" patient. Her father was also hospitalized with fever around February 2, but tested negative for nucleic acid and was not a clinically suspected case. He was recently discharged from the hospital with a common fever. So, the girl in black wasn't a close contact.

Community in the long-term divided into support for the property and against the two groups of people. Jiang often quarrels with the property, and on Feb. 20, when the reporter saw her again, she complained that she could only hear the rumbling sound when sterilizing, could not smell the smell of 84 disinfectant, and worried that it was just a formality. But, she said, it's not easy now, either.

The cause of the change is that the community closed, began to recruit group purchase volunteers. Jiang Xiaomei want to encourage other anti-property sisters to sign up, just let the property to see how they manage this community. But the sisters won't. Jiang Xiaomei is very angry. She wants to volunteer and go out shopping for the residents.

Qiu Lan is still apprehensive. She told reporters that the day before there is a community wechat group for help, is a woman, has been out of breath, living upstairs to the police Wang Nan, and later said it is not "new crown. ". Kiran couldn't figure out what was going on.

But Wang explained to reporters that he did not call the police, but the mayor's hotline. After a while, the community replied that the post was not from me, but from a friend of the woman's, who had listened to the woman's Gasp on the phone and called the police. In fact, the woman did have a "new crown" patient in her home, but she had been hospitalized 14 days earlier, and she was not a close contact.

Community out left turn is a hypermarket, three middle-aged men standing in the door, the sun hit their face. They are the community group purchase volunteers, waiting to move all kinds of goods. One of them said that the community does not recruit volunteers, a little more people, it will become a "crowd. ".

Liu did not take part in the volunteer activity. He felt that before he bought disinfectant products outside, and using a loudspeaker in the community to recruit volunteers, contact too much, the need to self-isolation at home.

But after a few days at home, he complained on Wechat, "I'm so bored. ". After the introduction of a friend, he decided to become a security volunteer.

On February 22, his assignment was to patrol the area around the shelter hospital, starting the night shift at 6 p.m.

Before setting out, Liu zhengkai is a little nervous, he is worried that some bad people spit at him. But, "never mind, I can MMA, if someone dare to do bad things at night, I will catch these bad guys. ".

He put on his Zhong Kui pendant.
